Name                          Purpose                                                           Java pattern or principle included
MessagingFacade               Public entry point to the messaging subsystem; coordinates        Facade, Single responsibility
                              validation, routing and sending

SendResult                    Represents the result of a send operation, including response     Single responsibility
                              code, message text, provider used, channels tried and total cost

MessageSenderFactory          Creates concrete message sender instances for each channel        Factory, Open/Closed principle
                              and provider (e.g. SMS, Email, Postal)

IMessageSender                Interface for all message senders in the chain                    Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle

BaseSender                    Abstract base class implementing common chain behaviour           Chain of Responsibility, Single responsibility
                              (holding next sender and delegating on failure)

TwilioSMSSender               Concrete SMS sender using the Twilio provider (stubbed with       Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle
                              System.out.println and simulated failures/costs)

CSoftSMSSender                Concrete SMS sender using the CSoft provider (stubbed with        Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle
                              System.out.println and simulated failures/costs)

SendGridEmailSender           Concrete email sender using a SendGrid‐like provider (stubbed     Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle
                              with System.out.println and simulated failures/costs)

SESEmailSender                Concrete email sender using an SES‐like provider (stubbed with    Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle
                              System.out.println and simulated failures/costs)

RoyalMailPostalSender         Concrete postal sender using a RoyalMail‐like provider (stubbed   Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle
                              with System.out.println and simulated failures/costs)

RoutingPolicy                 Encapsulates routing rules; decides the preferred order of        Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle
                              channels and providers based on message type and urgency

ChainBuilder                  Builds the chain of responsibility using RoutingPolicy and        Chain of Responsibility, Factory, Single responsibility
                              MessageSenderFactory

User                          Models an application user and aggregates all contact details     Single responsibility
                              (email, phone number, postal address)

EmailAddress                  Value object representing an email address                        Single responsibility

PhoneNumber                   Value object representing a phone number                          Single responsibility

PostalAddress                 Value object representing a postal address                        Single responsibility

Message                       Base class (or interface) for messages to be sent                 Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle

SMSMessage                    Concrete message type representing an SMS message                 Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle

EmailMessage                  Concrete message type representing an email message               Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle

PostalMessage                 Concrete message type representing a postal/letter message        Single responsibility, Open/Closed principle

ContactValidator              Coordinates validation of a User’s contact details using          Single responsibility
                              specialised validators

EmailValidator                Validates the format of email addresses                           Single responsibility

PhoneValidator                Validates the format of phone numbers                             Single responsibility

PostcodeValidator             Validates the format of postal codes                              Single responsibility

Main                          Program entry point; constructs the facade and dependencies       (Uses Facade, exercises Factory and
                              and runs scenarios to test all features of the messaging system   Chain of Responsibility, demonstrates SRP/OCP)
